Measuring Demand Generation Success for HR Tech
Sustainable demand generation requires understanding what's working and where improvements are needed. Effective HR tech demand generation measurement goes beyond simple lead counts and focuses on metrics that correlate with actual revenue outcomes.

Conversation quality matters more than conversation quantity. Are the HR leaders your demand generation programs reach actually able to influence solution decisions? Are you connecting with VP-level decision-makers and HR directors, or primarily with individual contributors who lack budget authority? Tracking the seniority and role of prospects engaged provides crucial insight into campaign effectiveness.

Pipeline velocity is another critical metric. How quickly are prospects from demand generation campaigns moving from initial conversations to later buying stages? If your demand generation efforts are reaching prospects in active evaluation phases, they should move through your sales process faster than prospects engaged at earlier awareness stages.

Deal quality and size also matter. Do HR tech deals sourced through demand generation campaigns have similar average values as deals from other sources? Do they close at higher rates? Do customers acquired through specific demand generation channels have longer retention and higher lifetime values? These metrics reveal whether your demand generation investments are attracting customers who represent genuine value.

